Feature: Venues list redesign for UIKit VenuesVC and SwiftUI VenuesMigration

Overview
- Apply the same redesigned venues list behavior to both:
  - UIKit surface: `VenuesVC`
  - SwiftUI surface: `VenuesMigration`
- Redesign is inspired by the expanded trending list style used by HomeVC.
- Venues are presented one per row (single-line list rhythm).
- Selecting a venue reveals venue details (including address) in a bottom details panel, without embedded map.
- Forward navigation is initiated from bottom panel action after venue selection (two-step tap flow).
- Preserve all existing function wiring and data/segue contracts.

Scope
- In scope: dual-surface visual hierarchy, row styling, details panel presentation, and selection polish for `VenuesVC` + `VenuesMigration`.
- Out of scope: backend contracts, map embedding in details panel, auth/session headers, payload changes.

Functional requirements

REQ-VEN-RD-1 Design baseline
- `VenuesVC` and `VenuesMigration` must follow `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venuesvc-redesign.prototype.html` as the review baseline.
- Inspiration sources include existing HomeVC expanded trending-list direction.

REQ-VEN-RD-2 Vertical venues list
- Render venues in a vertical list, one venue per row.
- Row layout should prioritize readability and tap affordance.
- Keep current data source behavior for movie-driven and map/admin flows.

REQ-VEN-RD-3 Expanded-list visual style parity
- Row spacing, typography hierarchy, and card/container treatment should align with the expanded-list visual direction.
- Both surfaces should present equivalent interaction/order semantics:
  - first tap selects row and updates bottom details
  - second tap from bottom CTA navigates forward

REQ-VEN-RD-4 Bottom details panel (no map)
- On row selection, show selected venue details in a bottom panel section.
- Bottom panel includes venue name and address.
- Do not embed map content in this panel.

REQ-VEN-RD-5 Navigate after selection
- Selection is explicit first step: row tap only selects and updates bottom details.
- Forward action is explicit second step: user taps bottom CTA to navigate to `VenuesDetailsVC`.
- Existing segue identifier and context propagation remain unchanged.

REQ-VEN-RD-6 Preserve existing functions/contracts
- Keep all current functions and handlers in `VenuesVC` operational.
- Keep `VenuesMigration` mode behavior intact (standard/admin/map), with redesign applied to standard list UX.
- Keep data manager interactions and field contracts unchanged.
- Keep existing behavior for admin/map flows and selection notifications.

REQ-VEN-RD-7 Back navigation retained
- Keep back button behavior and navigation semantics unchanged.

REQ-VEN-RD-8 Accessibility/readability
- Maintain clear contrast and touch target sizing.
- Details panel text remains readable in light/dark mode.

REQ-VEN-RD-9 Technology targets
- UIKit target: `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/VenuesVC.swift`.
- SwiftUI target: `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/VenuesMigration/VenuesMigration.swift`.
- This feature is complete only when both targets are aligned to the redesigned interaction model.

REQ-VEN-RD-10 Screen background and colors
- Screen background: white (#FFFFFF).
- Navigation buttons (Back, bottom CTA): black (#000000), text-filled.
- Row navigation indicators (chevrons › in venue list): grayscale light gray (#b7bfd3).
- All text: use NSAttributedString with configurable font family + size.
- Bottom CTA button: black (#000000) when enabled, disabled gray when no venue selected.

REQ-VEN-RD-11 Icon requirements
- Back button icon: left-pointing chevron (‹) or back arrow; 13px, black.
- Row navigation chevron: right-pointing › or chevron-right; 16px, light gray (#b7bfd3).
- Venue address metadata icons (optional visual): 📍 (location pin) or 🏠 (home); emoji or 16px asset.
- Bottom CTA icon: optional, navigation arrow pointing right; 12px, black.

Non-functional requirements

REQ-VEN-RD-NF-1 Performance
- List scrolling remains smooth with image loading.
- Redesign does not introduce repeated heavy setup in lifecycle callbacks.

REQ-VEN-RD-NF-2 Stability
- Existing venue selection, details update, and segue flow remain stable.

Acceptance criteria
- [ ] Prototype exists at `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venuesvc-redesign.prototype.html`.
- [ ] Venues are shown as a polished vertical one-row-per-venue list.
- [ ] Selected venue shows bottom details panel with address and no map embed.
- [ ] First tap selects venue and updates bottom details; second tap on bottom CTA navigates to `VenuesDetailsVC`.
- [ ] Existing functions and contracts are explicitly preserved.
- [ ] `VenuesVC` (UIKit) implements the redesigned behavior.
- [ ] `VenuesMigration` (SwiftUI) implements equivalent redesigned behavior.

Reference files
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/venuesvc-redesign.prototype.html`
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/speckit.swiftuifeatures.homevc-trending-carousel.specify`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/VenuesVC.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/VenuesMigration/VenuesMigration.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/VenuesDetailsVC.swift`

